The rummers love the crowded places and do not reject the sweets.
Renting a car, depending on the brand, will cost from $37 (Hyundai Getz) to $188 (Audi A6, Volvo S80) per day.
In addition to insurance, it goes out for $15 a day.
And renting a bike will leave you for 15 shekels a day.
The entrances to the museums cost an average of 30 shekels.
Israel in Numbers
In 2012, more than three million tourists from all over the world visited Israel.
Most of those who arrived to travel and rest were citizens of the United States, Russia, France, Germany, Italy, the United Kingdom and Ukraine.
