What have you met so far?
In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities everything works better than here; in Russia we have witnessed that in the east there is a long way to go.
Unlike Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there it is still not uncommon for a person to travel alone through the city center in an electric wheelchair.
Something as common as it is, for example, giving preference to someone in wheelchairs in elevators, there it is not.
