In what areas should we take the example of more developed countries?
There are many aspects that we're going behind...
But it is important to mention that the improvement and improvement of the situation always depends on the persons to whom it directly affects.
In London and Madrid it is very normal that people with a serious disability move on their own in public and can go to service, to the museum, wherever they want...
But it is not very common for a large number of people with disabilities to participate actively in social life, in this respect, with The Tap Tap we go a little ahead!
A respectful or barrier-free society is one thing, but when the time comes when eminent sportsmen, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers will start to change everything really.
So far, these are isolated cases of people who have great willpower.
